The Resolution of the Cabinet of Ministers of the Republic of Uzbekistan was adopted from October 5, 2019 № 849 "On approval of the Regulation on the Center for the Development of Investment Projects under the Ministry of Investments and Foreign Trade of the Republic of Uzbekistan"

The Regulation defines the main tasks, functions, rights and responsibilities, organizational foundations of the activities of the Center for the Development of Investment Projects under the Ministry of Investment and Foreign Trade of the Republic of Uzbekistan.

The main tasks of the Center are:

1) identification and development of new investment projects;
2) development of investment projects for modernization, technical and technological re-equipment of existing production facilities and promising enterprises, as well as promotion of high-quality and competitive products on the world market to foreign markets;
3) development and implementation of an interactive investment map of the Republic of Uzbekistan;
4) formation of a database of necessary licensing programs and systems for technical support of investment projects, as well as development in accordance with international standards of feasibility studies;
5) development and submission of investment projects to the Ministry of Investments and Foreign Trade of the Republic of Uzbekistan and the Agency for Attracting Foreign Investments under the Ministry of Investments and Foreign Trade of the Republic of Uzbekistan, if necessary, with the organization of preparation of proposals and presentations, including with preliminary feasibility studies, for attracting potential investors.

